author: Ha876
title: Smallish orange thing
review: This set is basically 17 orange pieces and 1 green piece for 2 bucks. There is really nothing special about this set. It is what the title says it is. The pieces are not bad though, but for 2 bucks, i don't think its worth it.

author: AETerry
title: Halloween Pumpkin Review
review:
Strangely enough I got this in my stocking for Christmas...

 

It's a good little set, I plan to set it aside for my Halloween decorations, it provided a quick, easy building experience for me. I suppose the best part is the ability to get several orange pieces that I just don't have a whole lot of. There's not too much you can do with it after words though except set it somewhere for display. Still, as a gift or small stocking stuffer, this was fun to get.

author: dartiss
title: A freebie from Legoland but not worth buying
review:
Received this set in a paper bag from Legoland Windsor as part of their Halloween themed Monster Street.

It was free, and probably best as there's really not much to it. No instructions but worked it out from images online.
